sentences.english: He creates a Five- Five teaching mode which is appreciated by the education circle.
sentences.chinese: 自創五五制教學模式深得教育界肯定。

sentences.english: He abdicated the throne in 1955 to play an active political role as prime minister.
sentences.chinese: 他一九五五年遜位，以首相身分從事積極的政治活動。

sentences.english: Japan sets up "the government form of Fifth Five-Year Plan Period" after the war, requires educational liberalization.
sentences.chinese: 日本戰後建立“五五政體”，要求教育自由化。

sentences.english: Thirty-odd of us, in group of threes and fives, strolled wherever we liked.
sentences.chinese: 三十幾個人，三三五五，各自在愛去的地方溜達。

sentences.english: The political candidate has a fifty-fifty chance of winning the election.
sentences.chinese: 那位政黨候選人當選的機率爲五五波。
